Package: structureR
Title: Factor-Vine Hierarchical Copula Modeling for Single-Cell Data
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R:
    person("GW", "McElfresh", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "gwmcelfresh@users.noreply.github.com")
Description: Models multi-level dependencies in single-cell data using
    Factor-Vine Hierarchical Copulas. Extracts three distinct data layers
    from a Seurat Object -- subject-level metadata, computed cellular
    proportions, and gene expression -- and fits a hierarchical dependency
    structure that isolates a dominant covariate (e.g., disease state) as a
    latent or primary factor. Provides tools for marginal transformation,
    vine fitting, and counterfactual simulation.
